                <head>21. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Following the outbreak of the Six-Day War on June 5, 1967, all Arab states
                    officially embargoed oil shipments bound for the United States, the United
                    Kingdom, and West Germany. For documentation on the embargo, see <ref
                        target="frus1964-68v34#d228">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1964–1968, volume XXXIV, Documents
                        228</ref> ff. For documentation relating to the Six-Day War, see <ref
                        target="frus1964-68v19">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1964–1968, volume XIX</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
